Interface ValueStructure<C extends ValueStructure.Container,I extends ValueStructure.Item>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    QuantityPriceAmountStructure
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    CategoryHolding<C,I>, Holding<C,I>

    public interface ValueStructure<C extends ValueStructure.Container,I extends ValueStructure.Item>
extends QuantityPriceAmountStructure
    A ValueStructure represents some sort of content (that has value). It has references to its Item (what is held) and Container (where is it held). Think of a ValueStructure.Container as a Portfolio and a ValueStructure.Item as an instrument/asset, but they really could be anything.
